    "body": "Most of Cython uses the error(...) method so that the maximum number of errors are reported to the user on each pass. Buffers don't do this, as illustrated by the todo item at http://hg.cython.org/cython-devel/file/cbcacc42eca5/tests/errors/e_bufaccess.pyx#l1 . At the very least, we could catch the ComplileError sooner and try to keep going. \n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/580",
